{
  "texts": [
    "Note that, difflib.SequenceMatcher is a class in the difflib module of the Python Standard Library.",
    "It is based on the Ratcliff-Obershelp algorithm, to compare sequences of elements, such as strings, lists, or any other iterable objects, and find the similarities and differences between them.",
    "All data analysis was performed with Python and is reproducible using the code linked below in the \"Code availability\" section.",
    "All the data used was obtained as described in the \"Data availability\" section.",
    "We estimate confidence intervals using non-parametric bootstrapping: for each evaluation metric, we generate 1000 bootstrap replicates by repeatedly sampling with replacement from the original dataset, where each replicate has the same size n as the original dataset."
  ]
}